[3] Cholera - Nepal (Far Western Region)
Date: Sun 22 Jul 2012
Source: The Himalayan Times [edited]
http://www.thehimalayantimes.com/fullNews.php?headline=Cholera+epidemic+looms+large+in+Doti&NewsID=340591


With authorities failing to contain the spread of large numbers of diarrhea cases in Doti since mid-June 2012, health workers today, 22 Jul 2012, confirmed the spread of cholera, saying it might soon become an epidemic if corrective measures are not taken quickly. Local residents have been terrified, and health workers are worried as the infection could not be controlled with their limited resources.

The spread of disease in Durgamandau, Gajari, and Ladagada VDCs (village development committees) continued unabated this week as it could not be timely controlled. Earlier, in places like Bagalek, Kalena, Dipayal Silgadi municipality, Kadama-ndau, and Sanagaun VDCs, where large numbers of patients suffered, the disease showed little signs of improvement as it could not be contained.

8 persons who lost their lives in Doti were initially believed to be cases of diarrhea, but now it was confirmed that they died of cholera after their reports of stool tests came to public knowledge. According to Kumar Pra-sad Dahal of the Epidemiology and Disease Control Division, Kathmandu, among the 17 stool tests from Doti, 5 have been proven to be cholera.

All the governmental and non-governmental organizations have reached the affected areas and have been involved in awareness programs.

