[4] Shigellosis - Taiwan ex Philippines
Date: Tue 3 Jul 2012
Source: Focus Taiwan [edited]
http://focustaiwan.tw/ShowNews/WebNews_Detail.aspx?Type=aLIV&ID=201207030015


Three Taiwanese tourists who traveled to the Philippine resort island of Boracay have been diagnosed with shigellosis, or bacillary dysentery, the [Taiwan] Centers for Disease Control (CDC) said on Tue 3 Jul 2012. Food may have been the source of infection, according to a preliminary investigation, said [Taiwan] CDC Deputy Director General Chou Jih-haw.

The patients, who were traveling with 3 different tour groups from 19 to 24 Jun 2012 are suspected to have eaten contaminated food at the same restaurants, he said.

The patients, a 21-year-old female and 2 males aged 34 and 48, had fever and diarrhea at the airport when they arrived home, the deputy director-general said. About 80 other members from the 3 tour groups were monitored for the foodborne disease, he said, and 18 were found with possible symptoms.

There have been 62 confirmed cases of bacillary dysentery in Taiwan in 2012 so far, 54 of which were imported cases from Indonesia, the Philippines, Cambodia, Viet Nam and China, according to the [Taiwan] CDC.

[Byline: Nancy Liu]

